<Body DocumentURI="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/ukpga/2004/34/body" IdURI="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/ukpga/2004/34/body" NumberOfProvisions="320" RestrictStartDate="2022-04-28"><Part DocumentURI="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/ukpga/2004/34/part/1" IdURI="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/ukpga/2004/34/part/1" NumberOfProvisions="55" id="part-1" RestrictExtent="E+W" RestrictStartDate="2018-04-06"><Number>
          <Strong>Part 1</Strong>
        </Number><Title>Housing conditions</Title>
        <Chapter DocumentURI="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/ukpga/2004/34/part/1/chapter/1" IdURI="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/ukpga/2004/34/part/1/chapter/1" NumberOfProvisions="10" id="part-1-chapter-1" RestrictStartDate="2018-04-06"><Number>Chapter 1</Number><Title>Enforcement of housing standards: general</Title><Pblock DocumentURI="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/ukpga/2004/34/part/1/chapter/1/crossheading/new-system-for-assessing-housing-conditions" IdURI="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/ukpga/2004/34/part/1/chapter/1/crossheading/new-system-for-assessing-housing-conditions" NumberOfProvisions="2" RestrictStartDate="2004-11-18" id="part-1-chapter-1-crossheading-new-system-for-assessing-housing-conditions"><Title><Emphasis>New system for assessing housing conditions</Emphasis></Title>
        <P1group RestrictStartDate="2006-04-06"><Title>New system for assessing housing conditions and enforcing housing standards</Title>
            <P1 DocumentURI="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/ukpga/2004/34/section/1" IdURI="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/ukpga/2004/34/section/1" id="section-1"><Pnumber PuncAfter="">
            <CommentaryRef Ref="c2050708"/>1</Pnumber>
                <P1para>
                    <P2 DocumentURI="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/ukpga/2004/34/section/1/1" IdURI="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/ukpga/2004/34/section/1/1" id="section-1-1"><Pnumber>1</Pnumber>
                        <P2para><Text>This Part provides—</Text>
                            <P3 DocumentURI="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/ukpga/2004/34/section/1/1/a" IdURI="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/ukpga/2004/34/section/1/1/a" id="section-1-1-a"><Pnumber>a</Pnumber>
                                <P3para><Text>for a new system of assessing the condition of residential premises, and</Text>
                                </P3para>
                            </P3>
                            <P3 DocumentURI="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/ukpga/2004/34/section/1/1/b" IdURI="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/ukpga/2004/34/section/1/1/b" id="section-1-1-b"><Pnumber>b</Pnumber><P3para><Text>for that system to be used in the enforcement of housing standards in relation to such premises.</Text>
                                </P3para>
                            </P3>
                        </P2para>
                    </P2>
                    <P2 DocumentURI="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/ukpga/2004/34/section/1/2" IdURI="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/ukpga/2004/34/section/1/2" id="section-1-2"><Pnumber>2</Pnumber>
                        <P2para><Text>The new system—</Text>
                            <P3 DocumentURI="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/ukpga/2004/34/section/1/2/a" IdURI="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/ukpga/2004/34/section/1/2/a" id="section-1-2-a"><Pnumber>a</Pnumber>
                                <P3para><Text>operates by reference to the existence of category 1 or category 2 hazards on residential premises (see section 2), and</Text>
                                </P3para>
                            </P3>
                            <P3 DocumentURI="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/ukpga/2004/34/section/1/2/b" IdURI="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/ukpga/2004/34/section/1/2/b" id="section-1-2-b"><Pnumber>b</Pnumber>
                                <P3para><Text>replaces the existing system based on the test of fitness for human habitation contained in section 604 of the Housing Act 1985 (c. 68).</Text>
                                </P3para>
                            </P3>
                        </P2para>
                    </P2>
                    <P2 DocumentURI="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/ukpga/2004/34/section/1/3" IdURI="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/ukpga/2004/34/section/1/3" id="section-1-3"><Pnumber>3</Pnumber>
                        <P2para><Text>The kinds of enforcement action which are to involve the use of the new system are—</Text>
                            <P3 DocumentURI="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/ukpga/2004/34/section/1/3/a" IdURI="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/ukpga/2004/34/section/1/3/a" id="section-1-3-a"><Pnumber>a</Pnumber>
                                <P3para><Text>the new kinds of enforcement action contained in Chapter 2 (improvement notices, prohibition orders and hazard awareness notices),</Text>
                                </P3para>
                            </P3>
                        </P2para>
                    </P2>
                </P1para>
            </P1>
        </P1group>
    </Pblock>
</Chapter>
</Part>
</Body>
<Schedules RestrictExtent="E+W" RestrictStartDate="2020-06-01"><Title>SCHEDULES</Title><Schedule DocumentURI="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/ukpga/2004/34/schedule/1" IdURI="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/ukpga/2004/34/schedule/1" NumberOfProvisions="20" id="schedule-1" RestrictStartDate="2013-07-01"><Number>SCHEDULE 1</Number><TitleBlock><Title>Procedure and appeals relating to improvement notices</Title></TitleBlock><Reference>Section 18</Reference>
<ScheduleBody><Part DocumentURI="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/ukpga/2004/34/schedule/1/part/1" IdURI="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/ukpga/2004/34/schedule/1/part/1" NumberOfProvisions="5" RestrictStartDate="2006-04-06" id="schedule-1-part-1"><Number><Strong>Part 1</Strong></Number><Title>Service of improvement notices</Title>
<Pblock DocumentURI="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/ukpga/2004/34/schedule/1/part/1/crossheading/service-of-improvement-notices-premises-licensed-under-part-2-or-3" IdURI="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/ukpga/2004/34/schedule/1/part/1/crossheading/service-of-improvement-notices-premises-licensed-under-part-2-or-3" NumberOfProvisions="1" RestrictStartDate="2006-04-06" id="schedule-1-part-1-crossheading-service-of-improvement-notices-premises-licensed-under-part-2-or-3"><Title><Emphasis>Service of improvement notices: premises licensed under Part 2 or 3</Emphasis></Title>
    <P1 DocumentURI="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/ukpga/2004/34/schedule/1/paragraph/1" IdURI="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/ukpga/2004/34/schedule/1/paragraph/1" RestrictStartDate="2006-04-06" id="schedule-1-paragraph-1"><Pnumber PuncAfter=""><CommentaryRef Ref="c2051523"/>1</Pnumber><P1para><P2 DocumentURI="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/ukpga/2004/34/schedule/1/paragraph/1/1" IdURI="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/ukpga/2004/34/schedule/1/paragraph/1/1" id="schedule-1-paragraph-1-1"><Pnumber>1</Pnumber>
    <P2para><Text>This paragraph applies where the specified premises in the case of an improvement notice are—</Text>
        <P3 DocumentURI="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/ukpga/2004/34/schedule/1/paragraph/1/1/a" IdURI="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/ukpga/2004/34/schedule/1/paragraph/1/1/a" id="schedule-1-paragraph-1-1-a"><Pnumber>a</Pnumber>
            <P3para><Text>a dwelling which is licensed under Part 3 of this Act, or</Text>
            </P3para>
        </P3>
    </P2para>
</P2>
</P1para>
</P1>
</Pblock>
</Part>
</ScheduleBody>
</Schedule>
</Schedules>
